Candied Kumquat
  --mom

1 qt kumquat
5 c cold water
2 c sugar + more for rolling
1/8 tsp cream of tartar

Wash kumquats & slit a coss in stem end of each. Cover fruit with 4 c cold water & bring slowly to boil. Simmer kumquats until tender, ~10 min. Drainwell. Buil 1 c of water & stir in sugar until dissolved. Add cream of tartar & boil mixture until it reaches 238F or until syrup spins a 3" thread. Add kumquats and cook 10 min. Remove from syrup and drain well (on rack until thickened). When cool enough to handle roll in sugar.

